Check if python is installed:
  bash: command -v foo >/dev/null 2>&1 || { echo >&2 "I require foo but it's not installed.  Aborting."; exit 1; }

Make venv if one does not exist:
  python -m venv venv

Temp change PATH:
  Windows:
    setlocal
    set PATH=...
    @REM Rest of your script
  Bash:
    export PATH="./venv/bin/:$PATH"

Install packages:
  python -m pip install -r requirements.txt

Run
